==English==
===Prepositional phrase===
'''[[off]] [[of]]'''

# {{italbrac|colloquial}} [[off]]; [[from]]
#:''I took this paper off of his desk.''

===Usage note===
*The use of ''off of'' as a preposition is considered incorrect by most authorities, and is not suitable for formal or business use.


----
Sometimes ''off of'' should be replaced with ''on''.
;Incorrect example 1:  Based ''off of'' quantum mechanics, an electron is both a wave and a particle. 
;Correct example 2: Based ''on'' quantum mechanics, an electron is both a wave and a particle.